text: I'm Katie Raby from Liverpool UK and I'm
a software engineer at a company called
cinch I started my career in marketing
and then about three years ago I decided
to transition into Tech so I did a
coding bootcamp in Manchester when I was
graduating from the coding boot camp I
really just wanted to differentiate
myself when it came to job applications
and I noticed there was a high demand
for cloud skills in the market
so that was when I got on to AWS skill
builder for the first time and started
working on my cloud practitioner exam
and what I love about skill Builder is
just the variety of different courses so
you can basically find something on
there for any AWS service that you might
want to learn about as well there's also
things like Cloud quest which is the
gamified learning which I'm just
obsessed with I just love how varied it
is in terms of you can be doing little
quizzes to reinforce your knowledge or
you can be doing Hands-On Labs which are
really similar to Real World experience
and real world problems personally skill
Builder has meant a lot to me because
it's really helped me gather all the
knowledge that I need for my exams and
my certifications but as well it's given
me knowledge which I take into my work
when I'm using AWS on a daily basis
we've had a new project recently and we
were going over and planning the new
architecture for the project effect and
I was going through the courses on skill
Builder that really gave me a good
grounding knowledge that I needed to put
it forward as an idea for this project
it was something that really benefited
the project and really improved the
architecture it reduced development time
and because we simplified the
architecture so it really benefits the
business and I can come up with new
ideas using the skills that I've learned
on the platform
